                  <msItem class="#versus #devotiones" n="1" xml:id="MS_Bodl_Rolls_16-item1">
                     <title key="work_13850" type="desc">Poem on the instruments of the passion ('Arma Christi')</title><bibl>(<ref target="https://www.dimev.net/record.php?recID=4083">DIMEV 4083</ref>)</bibl>
                     <explicit>That last shal witoutenn ende | Nowe Ihesu Criste vs thedyre sende Amen</explicit>
                    
                     <note>The last 102 lines of a poem on the Passion of Christ, with drawings (often
                        coloured) of the instruments of the Passion and similar subjects</note>
                        
                        <note>The text begins 'The cokke that krewe or hit were daye | When Ihesu Crist was in a fraye |
                        Chaunte for vs wit mylde Steuenne | That we mowe cum to the blisse of heuenn'</note>
                        
                     <textLang mainLang="enm">Middle English</textLang>
